OL,3,CAthletics stars want Government to
OL,4,Cback London bid for 2029 world
OL,5,Cchampionships
OL,7,FOlympic gold medallists Keely
OL,8,FHodgkinson and Sir Mo Farah are among
OL,9,Fmore than 100 athletes calling for the
OL,10,FPrime Minister to financially back a
OL,11,FLondon bid for the 2029 World
OL,12,FAthletics Championships.
OL,14,FIn a letter, penned one week before
OL,15,FChancellor Rachel Reeves presents her
OL,16,Fspending review, the authors argue the
OL,17,Fimpact of the event "goes far beyond
OL,18,Fmedals and headlines" and implore Sir
OL,19,FKeir Starmer to affirm Government's
OL,20,Fsupport because "the window to act is
OL,21,Fshort."
